<br>
If I were to make said changes, I would make more high level dungeons, not with mobs that hit so freakin hard you can’t breathe without slow, but dungeons with traps (not those lame ones in DN either – traps smart people can avoid or handle). There would be no xp bonus for zones. You would actually have to think to get through it. There would be no camps – you would have to keep moving, like HS was supposed to be. And it changed often – like mobs spawn, traps and surprises would spawn. There would be tons of content for one group. Not 72 people! <br>
<br>
The dungeons would work like the trials – where you say “I’m ready” and your one group gets put in and you move through – once the mobs in the first room are dead, you have to move to next room – no respawns til next group starts. A few minutes later the next group can come in and move through, etc.  The mobs get harder as you move through, and you can’t leave until you die or finish – no Gate, no CoH, no Evac.  <br>
<br>
Most of the gear would be recommended level (I love that so much compared to no drop). Decent drops, random off of all mobs – then the “boss” mob at the end has much nicer stuff.  It would take an hour or so to do the cycle. 12 groups, every 5 mins. Different dungeons would be different lengths. More spells and songs would be researchable, in addition to being dropped. <br>
<br>
Keys would be required for each dungeon, and would be quests more like the Seb key quest than the trials flags. There will be plenty of content for those that wish to level in DL type zones, and less spots suitable for kiting. I would program zone maximums, so that once a zone has a certain number of people, it stops letting new people zone in (rezzes would be the exception)(we’d work something out so it wouldn’t be exploited…) <br>
<br>
There would be stricter zone levels, so level 46 people couldn’t be in the zones designed for 55-65. And I would bring back the trivial loot code. Quest pieces would be flagged so as not to be affected by your level though. But there would be no lvl 60 pharming pp in Rathe – unless their twink does it. <br>
<br>
I would leave the end stuff for big guilds to someone else – not my area of interest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I just want a decent dungeon a lvl 62 bard can hunt in with her group…<br>
