<br>
There are certain higher lvl areas where a wipe without the ability to corpse summon is rotten prospect.  But in a Roleplay sense, good characters would be rare to ask an &quot;evil&quot; necromancer to use their magic to summon their corpse to them.  On some (all?) of the PvP servers mages get ability to summon corpses to offset that some &quot;teams&quot; can never have this ability otherwise.<br>
<br>
Killing in a plane such has Hate, Fear, Growth, etc. should have more &quot;in the rest of Norrath&quot; consequences.  Since priests and priest hybrd chars supposedly are granted spells from a diety, seems to me that a HE cleric who kills in PoG should get more of a smack-down then simply not being able to go to their home guild.  No ability to use imbued cultural items maybe?<br>
<br>
I also agree that reccomended/required level rather than no drop is nice for many items.  Trivial loot code is sort of two edged, IMO.  Lots of clerics don't camp Lord G in SolA before he is green... <br>
<br>
EDIT: Yeah, I know not many roleplay in EQ, it would just be nice if SoE put some game mechanics behind their words of &quot;we encourage everyone to roleplay.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosharafeadil>Roshara Feadil</A> at: 3/18/03 3:43:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grandmasterderil>Grandmaster Deril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/18/03 3:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5065.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www4.tripnet.se/~feline/div/deril/deril2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would I change?</span><hr size=1> Talking about graveyards and stuff....that reminds me of when I used to drag corpses through the Disco hall on a 'full pop', or, just run all the way ~ <p>&lt;img src=&quot;http://www4.tripnet.se/~feline/div/deril/deril2.gif&quot;      </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=timetoquiteq@thesaryrntavern>TimetoquitEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/19/03 2:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5065.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would I change?</span><hr size=1> Pretty simple, bump everyone to lvl 60.  Revamp all zones for lvl 60+ and forget about all the tirades.  Only thing left for everyone to raise would be AAXP, and 5 lvls.<br>
<br>
No more arguments about how the low end game is affected.  Heck!  There isn't a low end game anymore.  It's always just a rush to 65 in 99% of the cases.  There is no way they can give decent drops to regular mobs for mid-level people, you'll have tons of 60+ in the place farming it.<br>
<br>
Very few people bother doing the various quests from lvl 20 to 40.  They take too much time, when you can just jump over to the bazaar and get something better for very little pp, in most cases.  Where is the incentive?  If they make the quests yield good drops, then you have again the big brothers farming to sell them.  Solution?  There isn't one that can be implemented without changing the core of the game...and we all know that's not gonna happen.<br>
<br>
The system is flawed, we don't like it in many respects...but we've been playing for years and have enjoyed it despite all that!  The only possible fix is an entirely new game...about which we'll complain because this and that is not to our liking!<br>
<br>
This is just the way our civilization works...<br>
<br>
